SIMPLE: numb
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Numb
<hw>Numb</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nume</ets>, <ets>nome</ets>, prop., seized, taken, p. p. of
<ets>nimen</ets> to take, AS. <ets>niman</ets>, p. p. <ets>numen</ets>.
⟦root⟧7. See <er>Nimble</er>, <er>Nomad</er>, and cf.
<er>Benumb</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Enfeebled in, or destitute of, the power of
sensation and motion; rendered torpid; benumbed; insensible; <as>as, the
fingers or limbs are <ex>numb</ex> with cold</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A stony
image, cold and <xex>numb</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Producing numbness; benumbing; <as>as, the
<ex>numb</ex>, cold night</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Numb
<hw>Numb</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Numbed</conjf> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧md)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Numbing</conjf> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧m"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To
make numb; to deprive of the power of sensation or motion; to render
senseless or inert; to deaden; to benumb; to stupefy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For lazy winter <qex>numbs</qex> the laboring hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like dull narcotics, <qex>numbing</qex> pain.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Numbedness</ent>⟦br⟧
